cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.SD

This paper deals with analyzing data from an automated e-challan system for traffic violations in a metropolitan city. The analysis involves characterizing user behavior, identifying spatial and temporal patterns, and proposing a model for recidivism in traffic violations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the intersection of computer science and social issues. The paper also involves data analysis and machine learning, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.SD (Software Engineering and Programming Languages). Finally, the paper involves working with a large dataset, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases).
